ygData.messageBody:
Sure unless you have a caster, who typically has a HORRIBLE AC, in which
case fishing is less dangerous to your health, exp and lvl! =)

My enchanter also loved sitting around fishing, spamming myself with the
"You have no idea which direction you are facing" message, and practicing my
conjuration, evocation, divination, etc. as i fished for my chow. Costs 3cp
per grub to yield a meal that would cost 2sp for a fish or 1sp for a ration.
You do the math =)

Pava Rahti <Fellowship of Magic>
Bard of 23 measures
Cazic Thule


p.s. Why is everyone so obssessed with power leveling? Meet people... eat,
drink, be merry =)

>And if you spent the same time killing mobs you'd probably come out with
>more cash and more exp for the same time spent. Fishing at low levels is
>only worth the time spent on it if you put an extremely low value on
>your time.
